[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Link Collection Rust - High-Level Requirements
VERSION: 1.0

[SECTION]
TITLE: High-Level Requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-001-1
TITLE: Dump the contents into the console
STATEMENT: The system shall be able to read database files and output their contents to the console for inspection and debugging.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-001

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-001-2
TITLE: Use a fixed template to print to console
STATEMENT: The system shall support printing database contents using a predefined template format for consistent output.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-001

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-001-3
TITLE: Use any template to print to console
STATEMENT: The system shall allow users to specify custom templates for printing database contents to the console.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-001

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-001-4
TITLE: Read the existing date formats
STATEMENT: The system shall parse and handle multiple date formats present in existing database files.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-001

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-001-5
TITLE: Add the optional field 'Link'
STATEMENT: The system shall support reading and processing the optional 'Link' field from database records.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-001

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-006-1
TITLE: Use clap for top command and multiple subcommands
STATEMENT: The system shall use the clap crate for command-line argument parsing to support hierarchical commands and subcommands.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-002

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-006-2
TITLE: Add a logger
STATEMENT: The system shall include logging functionality for debugging and tracing application execution.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-002

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-006-3
TITLE: Add a configuration system
STATEMENT: The system shall provide configuration management to avoid repeating hardcoded values throughout the application.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-002

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-006-4
TITLE: Read the configuration from a file
STATEMENT: The system shall read configuration values from TOML files with support for multiple sources and priority levels.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-002

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-006-5
TITLE: List the tags from the database
STATEMENT: The system shall provide a command to list all tags present in the database with counts and metadata.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-002

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-002-1
TITLE: Add record from the CLI
STATEMENT: The system shall allow users to add new records to the database through command-line interface input.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-003

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-002-2
TITLE: Add record from a temporary file
STATEMENT: The system shall allow users to add new records to the database from temporary file uploads.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-003

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-002-3
TITLE: Print the record in the same order as it was provided
STATEMENT: The system shall maintain and respect the original field order when printing records that were added to the database.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-003

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-004-1
TITLE: Create a new stubbed HTTP server
STATEMENT: The system shall include a stubbed HTTP server for testing HackerNews download functionality.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-005

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-004-2
TITLE: Download the items from a URL
STATEMENT: The system shall fetch link items from a given HackerNews URL endpoint and parse the response.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-005

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-004-3
TITLE: Commit to git using the date of publishing
STATEMENT: The system shall create git commits for downloaded HackerNews items using their original publication date as the commit date.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-005

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: HLR-007-1
TITLE: Create Rust Stubs for existing Go Stubs
STATEMENT: The system shall replace all Go stub implementations with equivalent Rust implementations without changing external behavior.
STATUS: Approved
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SYSREQ-007
